#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:5
msgid "Units and Globally Available Variables"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:10
msgid "Ether Units"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:12
msgid ""
"A literal number can take a suffix of ``wei``, ``gwei`` or ``ether`` to "
"specify a subdenomination of Ether, where Ether numbers without a postfix "
"are assumed to be Wei."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:14
msgid ""
"assert(1 wei == 1);\n"
"assert(1 gwei == 1e9);\n"
"assert(1 ether == 1e18);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:21
msgid ""
"The only effect of the subdenomination suffix is a multiplication by a power "
"of ten."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:24
msgid ""
"The denominations ``finney`` and ``szabo`` have been removed in version "
"0.7.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:29
msgid "Time Units"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:31
msgid ""
"Suffixes like ``seconds``, ``minutes``, ``hours``, ``days`` and ``weeks`` "
"after literal numbers can be used to specify units of time where seconds are "
"the base unit and units are considered naively in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:35
msgid "``1 == 1 seconds``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:36
msgid "``1 minutes == 60 seconds``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:37
msgid "``1 hours == 60 minutes``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:38
msgid "``1 days == 24 hours``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:39
msgid "``1 weeks == 7 days``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:41
msgid ""
"Take care if you perform calendar calculations using these units, because "
"not every year equals 365 days and not even every day has 24 hours because "
"of `leap seconds <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leap_second>`_. Due to the "
"fact that leap seconds cannot be predicted, an exact calendar library has to "
"be updated by an external oracle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:48
msgid ""
"The suffix ``years`` has been removed in version 0.5.0 due to the reasons "
"above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:50
msgid ""
"These suffixes cannot be applied to variables. For example, if you want to "
"interpret a function parameter in days, you can in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:53
msgid ""
"function f(uint start, uint daysAfter) public {\n"
"    if (block.timestamp >= start + daysAfter * 1 days) {\n"
"        // ...\n"
"    }\n"
"}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:64
msgid "Special Variables and Functions"
msgstr "特殊變數與函式"

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:66
msgid ""
"There are special variables and functions which always exist in the global "
"namespace and are mainly used to provide information about the blockchain or "
"are general-use utility functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:74
msgid "Block and Transaction Properties"
msgstr "區與交易屬性"

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:76
msgid ""
"``blockhash(uint blockNumber) returns (bytes32)``: hash of the given block "
"when ``blocknumber`` is one of the 256 most recent blocks; otherwise returns "
"zero"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:77
msgid ""
"``blobhash(uint index) returns (bytes32)``: versioned hash of the ``index``-"
"th blob associated with the current transaction. A versioned hash consists "
"of a single byte representing the version (currently ``0x01``), followed by "
"the last 31 bytes of the SHA256 hash of the KZG commitment (`EIP-4844 "
"<https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4844>`_). Returns zero if no blob with "
"the given index exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:81
msgid ""
"``block.basefee`` (``uint``): current block's base fee (`EIP-3198 <https://"
"eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-3198>`_ and `EIP-1559 <https://eips.ethereum.org/"
"EIPS/eip-1559>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:82
msgid ""
"``block.blobbasefee`` (``uint``): current block's blob base fee (`EIP-7516 "
"<https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-7516>`_ and `EIP-4844 <https://eips."
"ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4844>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:83
msgid "``block.chainid`` (``uint``): current chain id"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:84
msgid "``block.coinbase`` (``address payable``): current block miner's address"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:85
msgid ""
"``block.difficulty`` (``uint``): current block difficulty (``EVM < Paris``). "
"For other EVM versions it behaves as a deprecated alias for ``block."
"prevrandao`` (`EIP-4399 <https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4399>`_ )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:86
msgid "``block.gaslimit`` (``uint``): current block gaslimit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:87
msgid "``block.number`` (``uint``): current block number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:88
msgid ""
"``block.prevrandao`` (``uint``): random number provided by the beacon chain "
"(``EVM >= Paris``)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:89
msgid ""
"``block.timestamp`` (``uint``): current block timestamp as seconds since "
"unix epoch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:90
msgid "``gasleft() returns (uint256)``: remaining gas"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:91
msgid "``msg.data`` (``bytes calldata``): complete calldata"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:92
msgid "``msg.sender`` (``address``): sender of the message (current call)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:93
msgid ""
"``msg.sig`` (``bytes4``): first four bytes of the calldata (i.e. function "
"identifier)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:94
msgid "``msg.value`` (``uint``): number of wei sent with the message"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:95
msgid "``tx.gasprice`` (``uint``): gas price of the transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:96
msgid ""
"``tx.origin`` (``address``): sender of the transaction (full call chain)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:99
msgid ""
"The values of all members of ``msg``, including ``msg.sender`` and ``msg."
"value`` can change for every **external** function call. This includes calls "
"to library functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:104
msgid ""
"When contracts are evaluated off-chain rather than in context of a "
"transaction included in a block, you should not assume that ``block.*`` and "
"``tx.*`` refer to values from any specific block or transaction. These "
"values are provided by the EVM implementation that executes the contract and "
"can be arbitrary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:110
msgid ""
"Do not rely on ``block.timestamp`` or ``blockhash`` as a source of "
"randomness, unless you know what you are doing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:113
msgid ""
"Both the timestamp and the block hash can be influenced by miners to some "
"degree. Bad actors in the mining community can for example run a casino "
"payout function on a chosen hash and just retry a different hash if they did "
"not receive any compensation, e.g. Ether."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:117
msgid ""
"The current block timestamp must be strictly larger than the timestamp of "
"the last block, but the only guarantee is that it will be somewhere between "
"the timestamps of two consecutive blocks in the canonical chain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:122
msgid ""
"The block hashes are not available for all blocks for scalability reasons. "
"You can only access the hashes of the most recent 256 blocks, all other "
"values will be zero."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:127
msgid ""
"The function ``blockhash`` was previously known as ``block.blockhash``, "
"which was deprecated in version 0.4.22 and removed in version 0.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:131
msgid ""
"The function ``gasleft`` was previously known as ``msg.gas``, which was "
"deprecated in version 0.4.21 and removed in version 0.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:135
msgid ""
"In version 0.7.0, the alias ``now`` (for ``block.timestamp``) was removed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:140
msgid "ABI Encoding and Decoding Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:142
msgid ""
"``abi.decode(bytes memory encodedData, (...)) returns (...)``: ABI-decodes "
"the given data, while the types are given in parentheses as second argument. "
"Example: ``(uint a, uint[2] memory b, bytes memory c) = abi.decode(data, "
"(uint, uint[2], bytes))``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:143
msgid ""
"``abi.encode(...) returns (bytes memory)``: ABI-encodes the given arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:144
msgid ""
"``abi.encodePacked(...) returns (bytes memory)``: Performs :ref:`packed "
"encoding <abi_packed_mode>` of the given arguments. Note that packed "
"encoding can be ambiguous!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:145
msgid ""
"``abi.encodeWithSelector(bytes4 selector, ...) returns (bytes memory)``: ABI-"
"encodes the given arguments starting from the second and prepends the given "
"four-byte selector"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:146
msgid ""
"``abi.encodeWithSignature(string memory signature, ...) returns (bytes "
"memory)``: Equivalent to ``abi."
"encodeWithSelector(bytes4(keccak256(bytes(signature))), ...)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:147
msgid ""
"``abi.encodeCall(function functionPointer, (...)) returns (bytes memory)``: "
"ABI-encodes a call to ``functionPointer`` with the arguments found in the "
"tuple. Performs a full type-check, ensuring the types match the function "
"signature. Result equals ``abi.encodeWithSelector(functionPointer.selector, "
"(...))``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:150
msgid ""
"These encoding functions can be used to craft data for external function "
"calls without actually calling an external function. Furthermore, "
"``keccak256(abi.encodePacked(a, b))`` is a way to compute the hash of "
"structured data (although be aware that it is possible to craft a \"hash "
"collision\" using different function parameter types)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:155
msgid ""
"See the documentation about the :ref:`ABI <ABI>` and the :ref:`tightly "
"packed encoding <abi_packed_mode>` for details about the encoding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:161
msgid "Members of bytes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:163
msgid ""
"``bytes.concat(...) returns (bytes memory)``: :ref:`Concatenates variable "
"number of bytes and bytes1, ..., bytes32 arguments to one byte array<bytes-"
"concat>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:168
msgid "Members of string"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:170
msgid ""
"``string.concat(...) returns (string memory)``: :ref:`Concatenates variable "
"number of string arguments to one string array<string-concat>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:176
msgid "Error Handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:178
msgid ""
"See the dedicated section on :ref:`assert and require<assert-and-require>` "
"for more details on error handling and when to use which function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:181
msgid "``assert(bool condition)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:182
msgid ""
"causes a Panic error and thus state change reversion if the condition is not "
"met - to be used for internal errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:184
msgid "``require(bool condition)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:185
msgid ""
"reverts if the condition is not met - to be used for errors in inputs or "
"external components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:187
msgid "``require(bool condition, string memory message)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:188
msgid ""
"reverts if the condition is not met - to be used for errors in inputs or "
"external components. Also provides an error message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:190
msgid "``revert()``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:191
msgid "abort execution and revert state changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:193
msgid "``revert(string memory reason)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:194
msgid ""
"abort execution and revert state changes, providing an explanatory string"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:201
msgid "Mathematical and Cryptographic Functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:203
msgid "``addmod(uint x, uint y, uint k) returns (uint)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:204
msgid ""
"compute ``(x + y) % k`` where the addition is performed with arbitrary "
"precision and does not wrap around at ``2**256``. Assert that ``k != 0`` "
"starting from version 0.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:206
msgid "``mulmod(uint x, uint y, uint k) returns (uint)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:207
msgid ""
"compute ``(x * y) % k`` where the multiplication is performed with arbitrary "
"precision and does not wrap around at ``2**256``. Assert that ``k != 0`` "
"starting from version 0.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:209
msgid "``keccak256(bytes memory) returns (bytes32)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:210
msgid "compute the Keccak-256 hash of the input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:214
msgid ""
"There used to be an alias for ``keccak256`` called ``sha3``, which was "
"removed in version 0.5.0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:216
msgid "``sha256(bytes memory) returns (bytes32)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:217
msgid "compute the SHA-256 hash of the input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:219
msgid "``ripemd160(bytes memory) returns (bytes20)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:220
msgid "compute RIPEMD-160 hash of the input"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:222
msgid ""
"``ecrecover(bytes32 hash, uint8 v, bytes32 r, bytes32 s) returns (address)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:223
msgid ""
"recover the address associated with the public key from elliptic curve "
"signature or return zero on error. The function parameters correspond to "
"ECDSA values of the signature:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:226
msgid "``r`` = first 32 bytes of signature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:227
msgid "``s`` = second 32 bytes of signature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:228
msgid "``v`` = final 1 byte of signature"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:230
msgid ""
"``ecrecover`` returns an ``address``, and not an ``address payable``. See :"
"ref:`address payable<address>` for conversion, in case you need to transfer "
"funds to the recovered address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:233
msgid ""
"For further details, read `example usage <https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/"
"questions/1777/workflow-on-signing-a-string-with-private-key-followed-by-"
"signature-verificatio>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:237
msgid ""
"If you use ``ecrecover``, be aware that a valid signature can be turned into "
"a different valid signature without requiring knowledge of the corresponding "
"private key. In the Homestead hard fork, this issue was fixed for "
"_transaction_ signatures (see `EIP-2 <https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/"
"eip-2#specification>`_), but the ecrecover function remained unchanged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:242
msgid ""
"This is usually not a problem unless you require signatures to be unique or "
"use them to identify items. OpenZeppelin has an `ECDSA helper library "
"<https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/api/utils#ECDSA>`_ that you can "
"use as a wrapper for ``ecrecover`` without this issue."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:247
msgid ""
"When running ``sha256``, ``ripemd160`` or ``ecrecover`` on a *private "
"blockchain*, you might encounter Out-of-Gas. This is because these functions "
"are implemented as \"precompiled contracts\" and only really exist after "
"they receive the first message (although their contract code is hardcoded). "
"Messages to non-existing contracts are more expensive and thus the execution "
"might run into an Out-of-Gas error. A workaround for this problem is to "
"first send Wei (1 for example) to each of the contracts before you use them "
"in your actual contracts. This is not an issue on the main or test net."
msgstr ""

