"send given amount of Wei to :ref:`address`, returns ``false`` on failure, "
"forwards 2300 gas stipend, not adjustable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:273
msgid ""
"``send()`` and ``transfer()`` are deprecated and scheduled for removal. See "
"the section on :ref:`send <send-address-member>` and :ref:`transfer <balance-"
"transfer-address-members>` for more information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:276
msgid "``<address>.call(bytes memory) returns (bool, bytes memory)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:277
msgid ""
"issue low-level ``CALL`` with the given payload, returns success condition "
"and return data, forwards all available gas (subject to additional limits "
"imposed by some EVM versions), adjustable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:280
msgid "``<address>.delegatecall(bytes memory) returns (bool, bytes memory)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:281
msgid ""
"issue low-level ``DELEGATECALL`` with the given payload, returns success "
"condition and return data, forwards all available gas (subject to additional "
"limits imposed by some EVM versions), adjustable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:284
msgid "``<address>.staticcall(bytes memory) returns (bool, bytes memory)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:285
msgid ""
"issue low-level ``STATICCALL`` with the given payload, returns success "
"condition and return data, forwards all available gas (subject to additional "
"limits imposed by some EVM versions), adjustable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:288
msgid "For more information, see the section on :ref:`address`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:291
msgid ""
"You should avoid using ``.call()`` whenever possible when executing another "
"contract function as it bypasses type checking, function existence check, "
"and argument packing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:295
msgid ""
"There are some dangers in using ``send``: The transfer fails if the call "
"stack depth is at 1024 (this can always be forced by the caller) and it also "
"fails if the recipient runs out of gas. So in order to make safe Ether "
"transfers, always check the return value of ``send``, use ``transfer`` or "
"even better: Use a pattern where the recipient withdraws the Ether."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:301
msgid ""
"Due to the fact that the EVM considers a call to a non-existing contract to "
"always succeed, Solidity includes an extra check using the ``extcodesize`` "
"opcode when performing external calls. This ensures that the contract that "
"is about to be called either actually exists (it contains code) or an "
"exception is raised."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:306
msgid ""
"The low-level calls which operate on addresses rather than contract "
"instances (i.e. ``.call()``, ``.delegatecall()``, ``.staticcall()``, ``."
"send()`` and ``.transfer()``) **do not** include this check, which makes "
"them cheaper in terms of gas but also less safe."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:311
msgid ""
"Prior to version 0.5.0, Solidity allowed address members to be accessed by a "
"contract instance, for example ``this.balance``. This is now forbidden and "
"an explicit conversion to address must be done: ``address(this).balance``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:315
msgid ""
"If state variables are accessed via a low-level delegatecall, the storage "
"layout of the two contracts must align in order for the called contract to "
"correctly access the storage variables of the calling contract by name. This "
"is of course not the case if storage pointers are passed as function "
"arguments as in the case for the high-level libraries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:321
msgid ""
"Prior to version 0.5.0, ``.call``, ``.delegatecall`` and ``.staticcall`` "
"only returned the success condition and not the return data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:325
msgid ""
"Prior to version 0.5.0, there was a member called ``callcode`` with similar "
"but slightly different semantics than ``delegatecall``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:332
