msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:334
msgid "``this`` (current contract's type)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:335
msgid "The current contract, explicitly convertible to :ref:`address`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:337
msgid "``super``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:338
msgid "A contract one level higher in the inheritance hierarchy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:340
msgid "``selfdestruct(address payable recipient)``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:341
msgid ""
"Destroy the current contract, sending its funds to the given :ref:`address` "
"and end execution. Note that ``selfdestruct`` has some peculiarities "
"inherited from the EVM:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:345
msgid "the receiving contract's receive function is not executed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:346
msgid ""
"the contract is only really destroyed at the end of the transaction and "
"``revert`` s might \"undo\" the destruction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:348
msgid ""
"Furthermore, all functions of the current contract are callable directly "
"including the current function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:351
msgid ""
"From ``EVM >= Cancun`` onwards, ``selfdestruct`` will **only** send all "
"Ether in the account to the given recipient and not destroy the contract. "
"However, when ``selfdestruct`` is called in the same transaction that "
"creates the contract calling it, the behaviour of ``selfdestruct`` before "
"Cancun hardfork (i.e., ``EVM <= Shanghai``) is preserved and will destroy "
"the current contract, deleting any data, including storage keys, code and "
"the account itself. See `EIP-6780 <https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/"
"eip-6780>`_ for more details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:357
msgid ""
"The new behaviour is the result of a network-wide change that affects all "
"contracts present on the Ethereum mainnet and testnets. It is important to "
"note that this change is dependent on the EVM version of the chain on which "
"the contract is deployed. The ``--evm-version`` setting used when compiling "
"the contract has no bearing on it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:363
msgid ""
"Also, note that the ``selfdestruct`` opcode has been deprecated in Solidity "
"version 0.8.18, as recommended by `EIP-6049 <https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/"
"eip-6049>`_. The deprecation is still in effect and the compiler will still "
"emit warnings on its use. Any use in newly deployed contracts is strongly "
"discouraged even if the new behavior is taken into account. Future changes "
"to the EVM might further reduce the functionality of the opcode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:370
msgid ""
"Prior to version 0.5.0, there was a function called ``suicide`` with the "
"same semantics as ``selfdestruct``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:378
msgid "Type Information"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:380
msgid ""
"The expression ``type(X)`` can be used to retrieve information about the "
"type ``X``. Currently, there is limited support for this feature (``X`` can "
"be either a contract or an integer type) but it might be expanded in the "
"future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:384
msgid "The following properties are available for a contract type ``C``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:386
msgid "``type(C).name``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:387
msgid "The name of the contract."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:389
msgid "``type(C).creationCode``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:390
msgid ""
"Memory byte array that contains the creation bytecode of the contract. This "
"can be used in inline assembly to build custom creation routines, especially "
"by using the ``create2`` opcode. This property can **not** be accessed in "
"the contract itself or any derived contract. It causes the bytecode to be "
"included in the bytecode of the call site and thus circular references like "
"that are not possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:397
msgid "``type(C).runtimeCode``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:398
msgid ""
"Memory byte array that contains the runtime bytecode of the contract. This "
"is the code that is usually deployed by the constructor of ``C``. If ``C`` "
"has a constructor that uses inline assembly, this might be different from "
"the actually deployed bytecode. Also note that libraries modify their "
"runtime bytecode at time of deployment to guard against regular calls. The "
"same restrictions as with ``.creationCode`` also apply for this property."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:407
msgid ""
"In addition to the properties above, the following properties are available "
"for an interface type ``I``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:410
msgid "``type(I).interfaceId``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:411
msgid ""
"A ``bytes4`` value containing the `EIP-165 <https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/"
"eip-165>`_ interface identifier of the given interface ``I``. This "
"identifier is defined as the ``XOR`` of all function selectors defined "
"within the interface itself - excluding all inherited functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:415
msgid "The following properties are available for an integer type ``T``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:417
msgid "``type(T).min``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:418
msgid "The smallest value representable by type ``T``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:420
msgid "``type(T).max``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:421
msgid "The largest value representable by type ``T``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:424
msgid "Reserved Keywords"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:426
msgid ""
"These keywords are reserved in Solidity. They might become part of the "
"syntax in the future:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../units-and-global-variables.rst:428
msgid ""
"``after``, ``alias``, ``apply``, ``auto``, ``byte``, ``case``, ``copyof``, "
"``default``, ``define``, ``final``, ``implements``, ``in``, ``inline``, "
"``let``, ``macro``, ``match``, ``mutable``, ``null``, ``of``, ``partial``, "
"``promise``, ``reference``, ``relocatable``, ``sealed``, ``sizeof``, "
"``static``, ``supports``, ``switch``, ``typedef``, ``typeof``, ``var``."
msgstr ""

